Amanda Khoza, News24 (ER24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - Two people, including a toddler, were killed in an accident on the N2 near Gateway, Umhlanga on Friday night, paramedics said. Netcare911 spokesperson Chris Botha said at around 20:00, paramedics responded to a scene where a vehicle had overturned. &nbsp;Paramedics found that the occupants had been ejected and they were located near the wreckage. An adult male, aged 35, was declared dead at the scene and a three-year-old girl had sustained life threatening injuries. Despite resuscitation efforts from the paramedics, she succumbed to her injuries. Botha said paramedics worked to stabilise a six-year-old-boy before he was transported to a Durban hospital for further treatment. Authorities are investigating the circumstances surrounding the accident.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.